page.title: 02ECOLOGY
page.content: SITE OF SCIENTIFIC INTEREST OWNED BY OXFORD UNIVERSITY.THIS AREA CONTAINS AQUATIC AND MARSHLAND PLANTS AND INSECTS.MANY OF THE UNUSUAL PLANTS ARE GRASSES AND IN ADDITION SEA LAVENDER, SLENDER HARES EAR,SEA CLOVER AND BEARD GRASS.INSECTS INCLUDE MEADOW BROWN BUTTERFLIES,DRAGONFLIES AND DAMSEL FLY.THE NEARBY ELMLEY MARSHES BIRD RESERVE IS RUN BY THE R.S.P.B. WHO ALSO LEASED THE SHOOTING RIGHTS OF THIS AREA FROM THE UNIVERSITY SINCE 1975. SQUARES 93/68 94/68 95/68 96/68 95/69 96/69 95/70 96/70
